  "prompt": "What are the best Shahrukh khan movies?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has had an illustrious career spanning several decades. Here are some of his most acclaimed and popular movies:\n\n1. **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)** - A classic romance that has become a cultural phenomenon in India.\n2. **My Name Is Khan (2010)** - A poignant drama addressing social issues and discrimination, with a powerful performance by Khan.\n3. **Dil Se (1998)** - A romantic thriller that features a compelling love story set against a backdrop of terrorism.\n4. **Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham (2001)** - A family drama that explores relationships and values, boasting an ensemble cast.\n5. **Chak De! India (2007)** - A sports film where Khan plays a coach of the Indian women's hockey team, inspiring them to victory.\n6. **Om Shanti Om (2007)** - A reincarnation drama filled with humor and song, celebrating the film industry itself.\n7. **Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi (2008)** - A romantic comedy that captures the essence of love and marriage in a unique way.\n8. **Devdas (2002)** - An epic tragedy based on the novel by Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay, showcasing lavish production and strong performances.\n9. **Jab Tak Hai Jaan (2012)** - A romantic drama exploring love and sacrifice, directed by the legendary Yash Chopra.\n10. **Fan (2016)** - A psychological thriller where Khan plays both a superstar and his obsessive fan, showcasing his versatility.\n\nThese films highlight not only Shah Rukh Khan's range as an actor but also his impact on Indian cinema. Each movie has a unique theme and showcases his talent in different genres.",
